====================================================
DATABASE MODELS (POSTGRESQL)
====================================================

Employee:
- id (PK)
- name
- role
- department
- manager_id
- joining_date
- status

Goal:
- id (PK)
- employee_id (FK)
- title
- type (KPI | OKR | MBO)
- progress_percentage
- due_date
- status

Review:
- id (PK)
- employee_id (FK)
- reviewer_id
- ratings (JSON)
- comments
- review_cycle
- created_at

Feedback360:
- id (PK)
- employee_id (FK)
- given_by
- score
- comment

PerformanceMetrics:
- employee_id (PK, FK)
- quantity_metrics (JSON)
- quality_metrics (JSON)
- efficiency_metrics (JSON)
- engagement_metrics (JSON)
- organizational_metrics (JSON)

AISummary:
- id (PK)
- employee_id (FK)
- summary_text
- generated_at

====================================================
REQUIRED REST API ENDPOINTS
====================================================

Employees:
- GET    /api/employees
- GET    /api/employees/{id}
- POST   /api/employees

Goals:
- GET    /api/goals/{employee_id}
- POST   /api/goals
- PUT    /api/goals/{id}

Reviews:
- GET    /api/reviews/{employee_id}
- POST   /api/reviews

Feedback:
- GET    /api/feedback/{employee_id}
- POST   /api/feedback

Metrics & Analytics:
- GET    /api/metrics/{employee_id}
- GET    /api/analytics/{employee_id}

AI:
- POST   /api/ai/performance-summary

====================================================
AI AGENT (MANDATORY)
====================================================

Implement ONE AI agent:
"Performance Review Agent"

Location:
app/agents/performance_review_agent.py

Responsibilities:
1. Accept employee_id
2. Fetch employee, goals, reviews, feedback, metrics from PostgreSQL
3. Build structured prompt (NO hardcoded text)
4. Call LLM to generate a professional HR performance review
5. Output must include:
   - Overall performance
   - Strengths
   - Improvement areas
   - Goal progress
   - Actionable recommendations
   - Motivational closing
6. Tone: professional HR language
7. Length: 180–250 words
8. Store summary in AISummary table
9. Return summary to frontend

====================================================
RAG READINESS (BACKEND ONLY)
====================================================

The architecture must allow future RAG integration for:
- HR policies
- Promotion guidelines
- Appraisal rules
- Training manuals

RAG must NOT replace the database.
Structured data stays in PostgreSQL.
RAG will only augment AI context.

====================================================
FRONTEND ↔ BACKEND CONNECTION RULES
====================================================

- Frontend communicates ONLY via REST APIs
- CORS must be enabled
- All responses must be JSON
- URLs follow: http://localhost:8000/api/*
- When selectedEmployeeId changes:
  - Backend serves employee‑specific data
  - All dashboards, analytics, and AI summary update dynamically

====================================================
SECURITY & BEST PRACTICES
====================================================

- Use .env for DB credentials and API keys
- Never hardcode secrets
- Enable FastAPI OpenAPI docs
- Add global error handling
- Backend must be authentication‑ready (JWT later)

====================================================
FINAL GOAL
====================================================

Deliver a clean, scalable FastAPI backend using Python and PostgreSQL
that perfectly integrates with the existing React frontend, replaces
all mock data, supports dynamic updates across all modules, and includes
an AI-powered (and RAG-ready) Performance Review Agent.
